  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This means that a system not only distinguishes itself from its environment but also differentiates internal components and processes within itself.",
    "For instance, within the scientific system, there are distinctions between different fields of research, methodologies, and the roles of individual researchers.",
    "These internal distinctions allow the system to organize and process information, in other words create order as part of its paradoxically unity with an indeterminate environment.",
    "The internal differentiation of a system, i.e., the systems within the observed primary system function autopoietically and fundamentally independently, but the relationship between these elements is maintained through the form of the observed primary system.",
    "In the scientific system, different fields of research (subsystems) operate independently with their own methodologies (criteria for validation) and theory (Luhmann 1989)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In the scientific system, different fields of research (subsystems) operate independently with their own methodologies (criteria for validation) and theory (Luhmann 1989)."
  ]
}